			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The name thing explains it all.
<br />

<br />
At some point in the past, NPC caster mobs with pets were probably judged to be too easy relative to melee mobs of the same level (which is still true). Perhaps there was an attempt to toughen up these NPC's by adding some "AI" code whereby "Froglok King"'s pet  would shield "Froglok King" when he got too low. But, because PC pets share much of the same code as mobs, they inherited this ability too.
<br />

<br />
Are there any charmable mobs in the game with names similar to our pet names? I know there used to be one in the hole, but he's gone now. If you can find such a mob, you can try having another mage or enchanter charm it, then see if your elemental pet of the same name will shield it when it gets too low.
<br />

<br />
The bottom line is that, in my opinion, PC warders and pets gained the ability to shield their owners quite unintentionally. Perhaps Rytan might want to elaborate <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=860634" target="_blank" class="postlink">Earnor</a></span></span>
<br />
65 Arch Convoker
<br />
Stormhammer</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
