			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This was one of the first AA's I bought with my 30 points saved for GoD when it came out. I have used it a ton since then and I can honestly say I really like it. I would like to ultimately max it at some point, its just very costly. First of all I made my "1" key a hotbutton for shared health, which is right next to my ESC key. So in an emergency I can hit ESC, 1, awfully darn fast. After a few weeks it's become second nature to be more aware of my pet's distance in relationship to me when things look like they could get bad, just takes some practice. Now it's almost automatic, add jumps me from behind I move forward to pet, ESC, 1, and watch the dps the add does to me go way down. 
<br />

<br />
Is it for uber raids? I dont know, I doubt it. Will it save you all the time? heck no. But it can buy you 3 seconds which is plenty extra time for a "good" cleric to put a quick heal on you. 
<br />

<br />
I reaaaaally like it for soloing. I was farming velks for threads for a friend and would just intentionally get a bunch of adds to bring in to AE, a few times my HP got a little scary, just shared health and you basically doubled your current HP. 
<br />

<br />
Its not a miracle, its not a 10k nuke or a pet with 20k hp, but it's a nice utility that has uses if you make it part of your mentally hard wired routine. So far my opinion is level 1 is great, just a tad short. Level 2 would be ideal for most bail out circumstances, leave it at that and work on other AAs. If you go beyond that, max it, and the technique becomes different. You'd tend to just hit it on inc of a train of mobs you weren't expecting, even if you're not getting hit, because it lasts like 60+ seconds maxed, then yourea "ready" if something gets out of control since it's already up. A lot of AA's for the priveledge, but cool nonetheless. 
<br />

<br />
I think a lot of mages are just lazy and think "it's not something I can just press a key and make me uber, so it sucks". No, it takes thought, timing, reflexes, maybe a little prediction. Awww shucks. <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="Sad" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
